        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 6:39AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 638 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 3 miles
east of Kosoma, moving northeast at 65 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Eubanks...                        Clayton Lake State Park...
Stanley...                        Snow...
Moyers...                         Nashoba...
Kiamichi...                       Kosoma...
Dunbar...                         Finley...
Tuskahoma...                      Clayton...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
